commit_message:
Add puppet-ciwatch to infra

CI Watch is a third-party CI monitoring dashboard that would be
deployed to ci-dashboard.o.o as outlined in
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/deploy-ci-dashboard.html

commit_message:
Fix usage of get_nailgun_cluster_nodes_by_roles()

method get_nailgun_cluster_nodes_by_roles() expects
list not string.

commit_message:
Increase timeout for env deletion over cli

In test delete cluster over cli we use
revert mechanism, but do not check if all the nodes
become online after revert. This lead to the situation
when cluster deletion takes a little bit more time.
So In this patch delete timeout was increased.
Also add check for node statuses after revert
and log with error level if some of them is offline.
We don't interrupt tests here according to cluster should be deleted,even all the nodes are offline

Change-Id: I769e5a17875595b632d111d6b5f1a782989e3a37
Closes-Bug: #1508007

networking-mlnx.

commit_message:
create_router cannot take enable_snat=False

When passing "enable_snat=False" to create_router, it is never set as
such in ext_gw_info, as the "if enable_snat" check fails.

Change-Id: I9cb0db672e27ce0664ce5544af3d14ba3c486c64
Closes-bug: #1490982

commit_message:
Fix setup-service script for RC/role checking

This patch adds checking related to RC file sourcing and user role
checking. Without these pre-conditions, the script cannot run properly.

Change-Id: Icfc3dd241cc57449712a56e7a11ef0b1b47c0826
Closes-Bug: #1470757

commit_message:
Optimize get_bridge_for_tap_device

Currently get_bridge_for_tap_device[1] iterates over all neutron bridges
and their interfaces.

This change proposes to deduce interface bridge from:

 /sys/class/net/%(interface)s/brif/bridge

which is a symlink to bridge interface path to improve performance.

[1] neutron.plugins.ml2.drivers.linuxbridge.agent.linuxbridge_neutron_agent

Closes-Bug: #1508789
Change-Id: Ia40cd81f47ff082a90d17f58514942ec50553241

commit_message:
Evacuate instance automatically

If nova-compute service is down by hardware failure,
an instance evacuate to another compute node automatically.
A super user is allowed to execute any script before or
after evacuation.

Blueprint: auto-evacuate-instance
Change-Id: Id164f0ff4a96382f9157d8c810c891a9e24ff763

commit_message:
Evacuate instance automatically

If nova-compute service is down by hardware failure,
an instance evacuate to another compute node automatically.
Add a new service named nova-saver.
A nova-saver is the service which monitors all enabled
compute hosts alive periodically and call 'evacuate instance'
for instances on the inactive hosts.

commit_message:
Don't update metadata_proxy if metadata is not enabled

When enable_metadata_proxy is false, the agent instance will
not have metadata_driver. And agent should avoid using it.

Change-Id: Ia18dc5dea23de49b97c8f225532531eb9232fb51
Closes-Bug: #1510399

commit_message:
Added log-store for the gate

This will allow us to review more logs from within the gate
job which will improve general debugging.

The log entry is created as a hard link

Change-Id: I598e12bc19d5715421b52ab8c3d3a0a1db1abd95
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-08 23:35:06.000000000', 'message': 'Added variable deprecation role and check

The change adds a role to check for variables that are in use which
have been deprecated. This change also brings within it an action
plugin with allows for the "warn" module to issues log entries for
items that are in use but have been deprecated. The new role can
be used as a dep to other roles and will react to the usage of
.*_fatal_deprecations being True.

The change was done in tree because it requires the use of an action
plugin to generate the messages. Action plugins are a server side
feature and can only carried in-tree.

The role was put into service with os_nova because its the only
role that has specifically called out items to be deprecated.
However the usage should be done everywhere such that we're able
to track and notify users that options are being removed.

Change-Id: I7cd87050f140535a01bd1a4111eb82c91daab318
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
'}, {'created': '2015-10-10 08:24:43.000000000', 'message': 'Added variable deprecation role and check

The change adds a role to check for variables that are in use which

plugin with allows for the "warn" module to issues log entries for
items that are in use but have been deprecated. The new role can
be used as a dep to other roles and will react to the usage of
.*_fatal_deprecations being True.

The change was done in tree because it requires the use of an action
plugin to generate the messages. Action plugins are a server side
feature and can only carried in-tree.

The role was put into service with os_nova because its the only
role that has specifically called out items to be deprecated.
However the usage should be done everywhere such that we're able
to track and notify users that options are being removed.

Partially implements: blueprint liberty-upgrade-path

'}]
commit_message:
Added variable deprecation role and check

The change adds a role to check for variables that are in use which
have been deprecated. This change also brings within it an action
plugin with allows for the "warn" module to issues log entries for
items that are in use but have been deprecated. The new role can
be used as a dep to other roles and will react to the usage of
.*_fatal_deprecations being True.

The change was done in tree because it requires the use of an action
plugin to generate the messages. Action plugins are a server side
feature and can only carried in-tree.

The role was put into service with os_nova because its the only
role that has specifically called out items to be deprecated.
However the usage should be done everywhere such that we're able
to track and notify users that options are being removed.

Partially implements: blueprint liberty-upgrade-path
Change-Id: I7cd87050f140535a01bd1a4111eb82c91daab318
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
VMware: Enforce min vCenter version

The VMDK driver deprecated vCenter versions less 5.1 in L
release. This patch enforces the minimum required vCenter
version for the VMDK driver.

DocImpact
  The minimum required vCenter version for the VMDK driver
  is 5.1.

Change-Id: I2ca0362623367d534b35124923947ee1e22c89fa

commit_message:
Fix functional tests fail on the env with https

The OS_CACERT environment variable should be passed to the test
environments to specify a CA bundle file to use in verifying a
TLS (https) server certificate.

Change-Id: Iee50946b34b7e285ebb7924cd5ac6cd83b355e48
Closes-Bug: #1511023

commit_message:
Avoid JsonPatch twice

apply_patch will convert patch parameter into JsonPatch, so we don't
need to do it. If we do, the parameter is JsonPatched twice.

Change-Id: I9f01089ee5f9a25c27d531ee60dc60a9c472c7fe
Closes-Bug: #1512206

commit_message:
Add -constraints for CI jobs

This adds the constraints factor to the base section and duplicates
the sections required for CI with -constraints as tox does not
currently support factors in sections.  Work towards enabling factor
support in sections is currently stalled, as such we will need to
duplicate sections adding -constraints to facilitate running sections
with the constrained install_command.

Implements Blueprint: Requirements-Management

Change-Id: I7afd52517750b82dcac94b8aae68dc0e94d00e54

commit_message:
Fix tag in liberty gate

The master gates on the "latest" tag as is Docker tradition. However
the stable branch has a set tag that is not "latest" so we override
that for the gate deploy.

Change-Id: Ia7b4c9fdcf3f840d8ecfd35f30aa37ccad08e3a5
Partially-Implements: blueprint functional-testing-gate

commit_message:
Use oslo_config new type PortOpt for port options

The oslo_config library provides new type PortOpt to validate the
range of port now.

commit_message:
Removes the use of mutables as default args

Passing mutable objects as default args is a known Python pitfall.
We'd better avoid this. This commit changes mutable default args with
None, then use 'arg = arg or {}', 'arg = arg or []'. For unit code which
doesn't use the args , just set with None. This commit also adds hacking
check.

This code was taken from commit 0bea84ac20fe498bd08f7212a0017196c8cb0812
in Nova.

Change-Id: I36d07cade687690dc02a8f6cc3d70f5d00caf112
Co-Authored-By: ChangBo Guo(gcb) <glongwave@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Avoiding usage of mutables as default arguments

Using Mutables objects as default arguments in function
definition is a known Python pitfall. This Hacking check
fixes the same in Neutron, and affects the corresponding
extensions which depend on Neutron's HACKING.rst file.

Change-Id: I02b4a41472a2e40919f65552fcb08d5482e72e4f
Closes-Bug: #1327473

commit_message:
Fix neutron resource cleanup issue

Fixes the neutron resource cleanup.
1). nova resource destroy should happen before neutron.
2). remove ports before router and net removal

Change-Id: I831a2cac28fae580de325f8700523b829653fc0f
Closes-bug: #1488757

[{'created': '2015-10-31 10:13:53.000000000', 'message': "Allow to update subnet without 'allocation_pools'

Heat allow to update 'allocation_pools' for subnet
resource in Change: I26f96f712dfa9405814e26a06668db7a608e84b8,
but the patch introduced a problem: if user remove the
'allocation_pools' from template when updating, heat will
pass 'allocation_pools=None' to neutron, but neutron doesn't
accept the None value for this property, an error will be
raised: BadRequest: Invalid input for allocation_pools.
Reason: Invalid data format for IP pool: 'None'. This patch
will pass [] to neutron to fix this problem.

Change-Id: I83e56d4494564de97717da6f6c0a9ae2cd9852dd
Closes-Bug: #1511909
"}, {'created': '2015-11-02 02:09:36.000000000', 'message': "Allow to update subnet without 'allocation_pools'

resource in Change: I26f96f712dfa9405814e26a06668db7a608e84b8,

accept the None value for this property, an error will be

Reason: Invalid data format for IP pool: 'None'. This patch

Change-Id: I83e56d4494564de97717da6f6c0a9ae2cd9852dd

"}]
commit_message:
Allow to update subnet without 'allocation_pools'

Heat allow to update 'allocation_pools' for subnet
resource in Change: I26f96f712dfa9405814e26a06668db7a608e84b8,
but the patch introduced a problem: if user remove the
'allocation_pools' from template when updating, heat will
pass 'allocation_pools=None' to neutron, but neutron doesn't
accept the None value for this property, an error will be
raised: BadRequest: Invalid input for allocation_pools.
Reason: Invalid data format for IP pool: 'None'. This patch
will pass [] to neutron to fix this problem.

Change-Id: I83e56d4494564de97717da6f6c0a9ae2cd9852dd
Closes-Bug: #1511909

commit_message:
Use correct constraint for allowed_address_pairs

Use constraint 'net_cidr' instead of 'ip_addr' for
ip_address in allowed_address_pairs because ip_address
accept a cidr as parameter.[1]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/8c3cb79aa54b0ffcdc840c7e95ab809835d05001/neutron/extensions/allowedaddresspairs.py#L85-L90

Closes-Bug: #1509962
Change-Id: Ica3ef0aa7a3ccab2a69e4f1e5bdb7bbd00e0699b

commit_message:
Fix _restore_local_vlan_map race

Local vlan mappings provisioned by _restore_local_vlan_map
might not be cleaned up properly if the corresponding ports are
removed before we enter the main loop.

This commit fixes the problem by making _restore_local_vlan_map
just record local vlan IDs and leave the rest of provisioning logic
to the main loop.

Closes-Bug: #1507776
Change-Id: I84ff6684ae3fda7d839c14b1a7382871f45ce610
(cherry picked from commit c69407e676c483820f5c505d8d6d7923b0461819)

commit_message:
Move retries out of ML2 plugin

There are several DB retry decorators in the ML2 plugin.
We want to keep them in the API layer as much possible so
this patch removes all but 1 and adds the retryrequest catch
to the API-level decorator.

The remaining one is the update_port_status which is an internal
RPC called method so it's not clear if there is a benefit to
moving it to the ml2 rpc file.

Change-Id: Ifffd424b693f57b5dd3de4dc625b50acc23abe0f
Closes-Bug: #1505908
(cherry picked from commit f6df2e704ba0c39e8a5ee59cb5fa1bd337deae82)

commit_message:
Set security group provider rule for icmpv6 RA in DVR

Security group provider rules for RA is set for the VM ports
when a router interface is added or updated after the VM
instance is created.

In the case of DVR Routers the security group provider rule
to allow the RA packets to flow through the VM port input
chain was missing and so the VM was not able to get a
SLAAC/DHCP address when associated with a DVR Router.

This fix will add the security group rule to the VM port input
chain to allow the RA packets to flow into the VM and hence
the VM will obtain an IP address assigned by the Router.

Closes-Bug: #1501969

Change-Id: Ib0b3499d9c880fe1462734b2d4092debf4819509
(cherry picked from commit a7dc528c1860f6a325a36bb7c633c60b635fc9a6)

Deepcopy port dict in dhcp rpc handler

changed dict in case of raising retry request.

commit_message:
Remove spurious logs from test_loguserdata

test_loguserdata wasn't a HeatTestCase based-tests, so printed some
useless logs to stdout. This fixes it.

Change-Id: Ib8a458ead43116f9a59709265405b9553c30f960

commit_message:
Retype support for CloudByte iSCSI cinder driver

This patch enables the volume retype function for CloudByte iSCSI cinder
driver. Admin can control the IOPS, graceallowed, compression and many
other QOS properties of a volume via OpenStack.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I4b05e49c545fb284e7abb90ad0661bcba5b646b7
Implements: blueprint cloudbyte-driver-support-retype

commit_message:
Add oslo_config "IPOpt" and  "PortOpt" support

The StrOpt modified to be IPOpt.Because oslo_config library
provides IPOpt type to validate the ip of range now

Change-Id: I01bbe76c48c1fd3bf3f9fe9e10a295cf13737c4a

commit_message:
Use assertIsNone(observed) instead of assertEqual(None, observed)

we should use the specific assertion:
  self.assertIsNone(observed)
instead of the generic assertion:
  self.assertEqual(None, observed)
as it raises more specific errors.

Closes-Bug: #1503055
Change-Id: If69026cc4437e584a26bbb85d7b40dcc4df79c05

commit_message:
Use assertTrue/False instead of assertEqual(T/F)

The usage of assertEqual(True/False, ***) should be changed to a more
meaningful format of assertTrue/False(***).

Closes-Bug: #1510001
Change-Id: I5203e9a8170d7af4e0cfac789f77a35d513d985a

commit_message:
run periodic-{name}-chef-rake-integration for master branch

* periodic-{name}-chef-rake-integration is currently broken, since $BRANCH gets
  not defined in periodic jobs by default but needed got gerrit-git-prep
* switch from gerrit-git-prep to  branch-git-prep with branch: master for
  periodic-{name}-chef-rake-integration to explicitly set the $BRANCH to clone
  to master

Change-Id: I54501cca8979669112bff5199c3c114cbaa3a6ad

commit_message:
Do nothing in prepare_for_replace if port not created

There is no need to reset 'fixed_ips' for an non-existent
port when prepare for update replace.

Change-Id: I212e3ff73e41c6bffc5e76457d8e2aaf360f5ceb
Closes-Bug: #1509977

Paul - this is a sad OpenStack review.

I feel that the person who experienced the issue should be linked to the patch that asserts it.

I fail to see how we are saving a patch."}, {'account_id': 1390, 'date': '2015-10-23 09:12:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Make version requirements more visible

The documentation was correct.  This table change helps
highlight that default packages are not recent enough
or too recent for the Kolla playbooks.

commit_message:
Add docs for create_server

create_server does a lot of passthrough to nova create_server, which is
great, but means it's tough to know what you need to pass in to shade
when reading the docs. List and document the parameters that shade is
supporting. Continue to support **kwargs pass through for others that
could be used but which shade doesn't know about.

Change-Id: I97cbb50f027e58766015b768a5da9c853b8c29fe

commit_message:
Adding multiple clusters creation

This new feature is being recently added to Sahara and this patch
updates the api reference to reflect the new api changes.

Change-Id: I85db7baf2f9d8c13e9fb16154566c5ef7a360bf6
Partially-implements: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/sahara/+spec/simultaneously-creating-multiple-clusters

commit_message:
Some prerequisites for Fedora OS is missing in zaqar README.rst

Add the missing packages which are required. Otherwise, it throws errors
while running the 'tox -e genconfig' command in the doc.

Change-Id: Ia1d59a042b6d1aa0ad140af0b270cbf098ae51df
Closes-Bug: #1507856

commit_message:
Rename pool to pool_group for flavor

Now the flavor's API is taking 'pool' as the parameter for
pool group. Obviously, it's really confused for end user.
This patch fixes it and changes related test cases.

APIImpact

Closes-Bug: #1492183

Change-Id: Ibf5051186002206bb28ed823c2a98a739639fb3a

commit_message:
Move ironic client attribute to correct class

The _ironic_client attribute is useful only for the OperatorCloud
class, so having it defined in OpenStackCloud is bad programming
style. Move it to where it is used.

Change-Id: I8141e1758e28a8120f0e78c9e407bb416a499166

commit_message:
Aligned a few words in the docs

We say "not supported" when the cloud doens't do something, but there
were two places where we used other words. Fix them. Also, make the
image properties a blockquote.

commit_message:
Timeout too aggressive for inspection tests

The new ironic inspection tests has a timeout that appears may
be too aggressively low, which may be causing the iterator to give
up before yielding even once, on a random basis.

Change-Id: I18d447e092c74e21edcc7f90f36112d8c87ffee7

commit_message:
Allow for templated variables in auth_url

Some clouds have auth_urls per region, which means putting a static
auth_url in the config file isn't going to work. Allow {} substitutions
in the auth_url so that other elements of the auth dict can be injected.
This will not solve _everything, but it will solve all of the currently
identified issues, and should be upwardly open if we need something
more complex later.

Change-Id: I6107d0669734647cfa0bef118bdf7739949991ad

[{'created': '2015-10-21 17:21:14.000000000', 'message': "Change section name for AMQP rabbit parameters

Parameter 'amqp_durable_queues' under section 'DEFAULT' now is
deprecated since Liberty and should be placed under certain

commit_message:
Change section name for AMQP rabbit parameters

Parameter 'amqp_durable_queues' under section 'DEFAULT' now is
deprecated since Liberty and should be placed under certain
rpc backend section [1,2]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/blob/stable/liberty/oslo_messaging/_drivers/amqp.py#L36
[2] http://docs.openstack.org/liberty/config-reference/content/configuring-rpc.html

Change-Id: I7d701bcc12efe66ab67932f799ee09d57c942217

I'm pretty sure we want neutron credentials here.  See bug tracker for mor edetails."}, {'account_id': 18980, 'date': '2015-11-01 10:25:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

How can this even work?
It is using nova/NEUTRON_PASS to authenticate with Keystone.
This can't be working as Keystone has no such user/pass combination.

I think it is either neutron/NEUTRON_PASS or nova/NOVA_PASS, and I would go for the latter, otherwise that would mean Nova has to know the credentials of the services he has to talk to (awkward)."}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-11-01 10:30:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

The username here:
https://github.com/openstack/kolla/blob/master/ansible/roles/nova/templates/nova.conf.j2#L105

should be neutron, not nova.'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-11-01 10:31:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

since both neutron and nova have admin, it doesn't matter.  If we trim permissions later so that neutron for example can only do networking specific things (I don't even know if that is possible?) then neutron would be the correct user."}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-11-01 10:32:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
unified policy file

A sample policy file that can work as the defaults for the
most central of OpenStack services.  This will not replace the current
defaults, but rather will be an option for the deployers to use when
moving to Dynamic Policy as the default.

Change-Id: I37c2f7f755bdb92e737341bd54178ba0d6bf491b

commit_message:
ovs_neutron_agent: display loaded extensions

Currently neutron agent-show command does not provide the visibility for the
loaded extensions. This commit fixes that.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Iab101682df4676ad3ca2531356a1de8f2a2d4f14
Closes-Bug: #1497969
(cherry picked from commit b7b6f3fe823994fdacde6e87a6a1f62692508fbe)

commit_message:
Downgrade "extended * dict" log messages to debug

These things are completely useless to operators. They
should not be logged at the INFO level. We can have a
separate debate about whether or not they should even
exist at all.

This patch is directly to Kilo because it was already
removed during another refactor.[1]

1. I20a249c47b58292125476bc44b2372ca959509e3

Change-Id: I6fc68f4afd8a54240352180212d6d1ddc6659d05

commit_message:
Create floating IP on a subnet ID

Documented creating of floating IP on a specific subnet in
an external network. Added the description and updated the
common.ent file with create floating IP Request parameters.

(df) corrected error for "list of xxx objects."
(df) updated language for floating IP on subnet

Closes-Bug: #1482496

commit_message:
rabbitmq: do not manage rabbitmq service anymore

rabbitmq_class was deprecated in the previous release, this patch drop it.

That means:

  * we are not installing rabbitmq service anymore.
  * rabbitmq_class parameter is deleted
  * port, cluster_disk_nodes and enabled parameters are deprecated for
    backward compatibility but port and cluster_disk_nodes have no effect
    since we don't install rabbitmq anymore.
  * unit tests are updated

Co-Authored-By: Emilien Macchi <emilien@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I373043294a4f3258799e613176725030fcbd2a50

commit_message:
Update vagrant support to use docker 1.9.0 rather experimental

Experimental docker changes very frequently and this can lead to unexpected
behavior. It will be better to use docker latest release rather experimental.

Change-Id: Ic40155a3788e37158df65d43bc8629f4f30a7bbf
Closes-bug: #1507447

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-22 15:58:12.000000000', 'message': "Try to use zuul-cloner to prepare fixtures

In OpenStack Infra, we would like to run Puppet unit tests that
sometimes depends on other Puppet OpenStack modules.
Example: a patch in puppet-openstacklib that needs to be tested in puppet-nova.

This patch modifies the Rakefile to:
* clean spec_prep and spec_clean Rake tasks
* use openstack/puppet-openstack-integration/install_modules_unit.sh script
  to clone modules.
* do not use .fixtures.yaml file to clone modules and rely on
  zuul-cloner or git.
* Add openstack/ in gitignore so we never commit the
  puppet-openstack-integration repository (can happen when spec_clean
  did not run but you want to submit the patch anyway)
* Allow to run a custom Puppetfile if PUPPETFILE env is exported. It
  will allow people to test the module with the dependencies they like,
  feature we had with .fixtures.yaml.

Also add 'r10k' to Gemfile.

That way, we will be able to use zuul dependencies and run tests accross
modules like we do with functional testing.

Change-Id: I7b5af3ea6b21009a505a8b6c49086d339eaa43e5

commit_message:
Try to use zuul-cloner to prepare fixtures

In OpenStack Infra, we would like to run Puppet unit tests that
sometimes depends on other Puppet OpenStack modules.
Example: a patch in puppet-openstacklib that needs to be tested in puppet-nova.

This patch modifies the Rakefile to:
* clean spec_prep and spec_clean Rake tasks
* use openstack/puppet-openstack-integration/install_modules_unit.sh script
  to clone modules.
* do not use .fixtures.yaml file to clone modules and rely on
  zuul-cloner or git.
* Add openstack/ in gitignore so we never commit the
  puppet-openstack-integration repository (can happen when spec_clean
  did not run but you want to submit the patch anyway)
* Allow to run a custom Puppetfile if PUPPETFILE env is exported. It
  will allow people to test the module with the dependencies they like,
  feature we had with .fixtures.yaml.

Also add 'r10k' to Gemfile.

That way, we will be able to use zuul dependencies and run tests accross
modules like we do with functional testing.

Change-Id: I7b5af3ea6b21009a505a8b6c49086d339eaa43e5

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html

Refactoring log utils

commit_message:
nova.conf: fix invalid neutron credentials

Nova should use the neutron account to interact with Neutron.

Change-Id: I55b89ac3c847e24bd4c121cf61f0db0ec413c2bb
Closes-Bug: #1512070

commit_message:
Remove deprecated nova_* options

Neutron nova_* options have been deprecated in Kilo in favour of options
in [nova] section.

This change removes these options in order to simplify code, clarify
configuration and avoid a warning in unittests.

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact
Closes-Bug: #1509092
Related-Bug: #1403686
Change-Id: I950f72ad7d7d41cfa006f8c7105934301cd56faa

versions of python may try to generate conflicting versions of the
.coverage file and fail to report.

commit_message:
Remove coverage files after each run

Coverage files should be erased after every run. Otherwise different
versions of python may try to generate conflicting versions of the
.coverage file and fail to report.

Coverage can still be run separately using tox's coverage target. It
will leave the files behind.

Change-Id: I7d1a4e9bb8195f331d8078fd45d65deae2175ff9

commit_message:
Add key size validator

Add a validator for the public key sizes. This allows to reject a
request with a 512b long RSA key for example.

Change-Id: Ib4988e595c4c5cdc643af56e9529e8c0de31d993

Make sure all test cases use only one certificate request so that it's
easier to manage/update. Also use the example.com domain for that
certificate.

commit_message:
Remove endpoint policy extensions that should be part of main keystone

As part of an effort to move keystone extensions into the main part of
keystone, I added [endpoint_policy] enabled = True, which should be the
default.  And removed the db_sync extension because it is part of the
main code and will be migrated along with the regular sync.

Change-Id: I0d7d06a15cdef722566d3902c45f6699c77160f8
Closes-Bug: 1459458

Consume /etc/openstack/clouds.yaml

commit_message:
Add karma-spec-reporter

While writing unit tests around our components I found it really
difficult to understand what was going on once a failure happened due to
the lacke of information given by karma progress reporter.
While talking to a few people on the community, found out that karma
spec reporter gives you better feedback.

Change-Id: I0a3278d7ff424e0b3218e3f7b1a2f8356eb51ceb

commit_message:
Fixed a bunch of typos throughout Neutron

Went through all of the docstrings in Neutron and did
some cleanup.  I'm sure there are bunch more that I have missed.

Change-Id: Ib29d2de1c580880c89ed4fd069e1515d0977a3e7

commit_message:
Add logic to support baremetal inspection

Ironic supports an inspect verb which directs ironic to boot
the node into a special firmware image in order to collect
properties from the remote node.

Change-Id: I4ba3f0cf4ad6f5466e52f5d034bb217f06eec7dd

commit_message:
node_set_provision_state wait/timeout support

Addition of wait/timeout support for node_set_provision_state to
block the method until the machine has entered the desired state.

Combined with this, node_set_provision_state will now return the
state of the machine as opposed to just passing through the default
from the ironicclient node set provision state call.

Change-Id: I3e0bfe9e4612291dc77bd683479f7f99aef50d0a

commit_message:
Fixing job execution creation with is_protected field

Now job execution can be created with is_protected
parameter set to True

Change-Id: Id4478bcc22cff58cb868ba5890d281aec52013a3
Closes-bug: #1510994

commit_message:
Revert "Handle correct exception raised by python-novaclient"

This reverts commit 99dc6d34754954a27f6998406a94743c41b93981

With the block on novaclient 2.33 we can undo this workaround.
The regression in novaclient was reverted and will be in the next
release.

Change-Id: If561b699eb04486660009f100c5db425c3586d3c
Related-Bug: #1510790

ok, i added tests for it. it was a bit tricky b/c you can't pass an invalid parameter value when the parameter is instantiated in new_parameter b/c .parsed is called there, which bypasses ._validate. So you'd get the ValueError raised, instead of the StackValidationError I'm looking for.

I went around that by instantiating the parameter with a valid value, then setting .user_value to something invalid, then checking .validate.

let me know if that sounds right"}, {'account_id': 7144, 'date': '2015-10-14 21:25:43.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-14 22:31:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

commit_message:
Raise StackValidationFailed on parameter validation

This changes the _validate methods for the JsonParam and
CommaDelimitedListParam to raise StackValidationFailed execeptions if
the parameters values fail to parse. A failure to parse will be
indicated with a ValueError exception, so that exception is caught and
StackValidationFailed is raised instead.

This brings these parameters in line with the behavior in the other
parameter type classes.

It also makes the validation failures much more helpful to users with
stacks with lots of parameters (TripleO), as the name of the parameter
that failed validation will now be logged as part of the exception.

Change-Id: Ife08272f0e95491c030e5d70499fe31d462c515c

commit_message:
Fix home button in 500 page

Currently, 500 page uses WEBROOT to set home link where WEBROOT is being taken
from horizon.conf module. However, this module sets only HORIZON_CONFIG.
As a result, 500 page is rendered with empty link, pointing home button
to current page.

This patch loads WEBROOT to horizon.conf, so it can be used in template
for 500 error page.

Change-Id: Icdd23703527a09a61d1326992b25a1004713444e
Closes-Bug: 1507563

commit_message:
Decompose ML2 mechanism driver for OVSvApp

This change removes OVSvApp ML2 mechanism driver after its definition in
networking-vsphere.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1511198
Depends-On: Ib7b2852f3d4dc35a837a425366c5bf0135725a74

- gate-glanceclient-dsvm-functional http://logs.openstack.org/69/220969/2/check/gate-glanceclient-dsvm-functional/47ff0b9/ : SUCCESS in 20m 14s'}, {'account_id': 17116, 'date': '2015-09-11 12:59:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Should the server not just send back an empty locations list, rather than just attempting to set an location anyway and potentially getting a 400 error?'}, {'account_id': 12363, 'date': '2015-09-11 13:27:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 15054, 'date': '2015-09-14 12:35:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

@Niall, Could you explain more? IMO, if images doesn't have locations, we may not check it."}, {'account_id': 17116, 'date': '2015-09-14 13:31:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I thought that if the server did not respond with locations it meant that it had not been enabled in the configuration files (from my understanding of the documentation).
Therefore if there are no locations it will fail anyway.

If this is not the case, and the sever does not respond with a location has been enabled, maybe that is the change we should make server side. As this would save a second request just to make sure that it is not enabled as it would be covered in the first response.'}, {'account_id': 15054, 'date': '2015-09-15 01:47:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

@Niall,do you mean 'show_image_direct_url' config? I tested it.
Set show_image_direct_url = True. 
1. The queued images still return without location.  
2. The active images return 'direct_url' instead of locations.

In both situations, 'glance location-add'  raise the same error.

Or you mean any other config items? I didn't find one. Please point out it to me. Thanks.

So IMO, we should fix it either like this patch or let glance return imges with locations,not 'direct_url',if permitted in config item(Need your help to point out which one). Or let client check 'direct_url', not 'locations'."}, {'account_id': 17116, 'date': '2015-09-15 13:05:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

I couldn't find what i read before, however I found this:

https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/api/v2/images.py#L735-L750 

The comment in that section mentions that an empty list should be returned even when no locations have been set.

Therefore I think the expected behavior is for the sever to return an empty list."}, {'account_id': 15054, 'date': '2015-09-15 15:02:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Got it. So we should forbid location add when the config is False,like client does. Am I right?'}, {'account_id': 15054, 'date': '2015-09-15 15:12:03.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

This should fix in glance, not client'}, {'account_id': 17116, 'date': '2015-09-15 15:51:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Yeah, I think this is a server problem.'}, {'account_id': 8289, 'date': '2015-10-31 07:35:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

See the comment in lauchpad, I prefer to remove the constraint 
from glanceclientv2, to make sure heat can migrate to glance v2 backward compatible.'}]

commit_message:
Fix wrong check when add locations to image

Now,when add a new location to a image, it will return an error:
'The administrator has disabled API access to image locations'

But the 'queued' image maybe doesn't have 'locations' property
in some case. So we should not check the existent of 'locations'
when add a new one.

Change-Id: If48088297531c789b4af799bf021bac7d281061a
Closes-bug: #1493026

commit_message:
Detach volume on device validation failure

If device validation fails when attaching a volume for some driver
operation (copy_volume_data, copy_image_to_volume, copy_volume_to_image)
we may end up with an attached volume that we don't cleanup.

This patch tries to detach the volume if we fail when validating the
device after we have attached the volume.

This happens for example on multipath when we have properly detected the
paths but they are all in a failed state when we try to read from the
device on validation.

Closes-Bug: #1502138
Change-Id: I73be4206930eba7da064e22d86ff2136191acb0b
(cherry picked from commit c5323c6d6c9ec6628cd38e21f11ba45bfeb7867f)

commit_message:
Translation setup

To start translation, we need to initially import the
translation file - and place it at the proper place so that
the usual CI scripts can handle it.

The proper place is for all python projects
$PROJECT/locale/$PROJECT.pot - see setup.cfg.

Further imports will be done by the OpenStack Proposal bot.

Note that translations have been setup already on infra side as part of
initial repo setup. This change is necessary so that the scripts
actually do what they should do.

Closes-Bug: #1511306
Change-Id: Ie518bffe825ae1c6d139a0613c30bc9748b52cd7

commit_message:
Change section name for AMQP rabbit parameters

Parameter 'amqp_durable_queues' under section 'DEFAULT' now is
deprecated since Liberty and should be placed under certain
rpc backend section [1,2]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/blob/liberty/oslo_messaging/_drivers/amqp.py#L36
[2] http://docs.openstack.org/liberty/config-reference/content/configuring-rpc.html

Change-Id: Iecef3c80afe38a908585db9563da417c445d0665

commit_message:
Fixing default_facts merge

Prior to this change, we were incorrectly using merge! on the
@default_facts. This would eventually lead to weird testing issues if
@default_facts was ever reused within a test run. merge!(...) will
update the @default_facts variable and we want to use merge(...) so that
we are not updating the @default_facts variable.

Change-Id: I55b518ee4af1a76ff5fc0e071410ccee5e4dfb34

commit_message:
Prepare cred_client for migration

Prepare the cred_client module for migration to tempest-lib,
by removing dependencies from config (indirectly via
removing dependencies from the credentials module), and also
by using tempest-lib only exceptions.

Migration to tempest lib canont take place until the idenity
clients are migrated to tempest.

Change-Id: Iad84f84faff71d1e7d7f4fa06b4e467b1d4b94f0

commit_message:
Fix unit tests for migration

Prepare credential providers unit tests for migration:
- move dynamic_creds tests to the right folder
- rename tenant_isolation variable to dynamic_creds in admin_available
- create missing tests for alt_available

Change-Id: Ib8dcdd1671b3d107a6358b8b0b5a1639485161c5

Fix the return values of create and delete volume

also fixes the delete function so it uses get_volume() instead of
the volume_exists() function

[{'account_id': 19092, 'date': '2015-10-30 18:42:00.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 10068, 'date': '2015-10-30 18:42:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html
    Commit Messages: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/GitCommitMessages"}, {'account_id': 19092, 'date': '2015-10-30 18:45:24.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 19092, 'date': '2015-10-30 18:47:33.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-30 18:54:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

commit_message:
[Admin-guide-cloud] Move section and add note

Per blueprint, moved the Networking Arch section
under the Intro section to keep conceptual
overview topics together. Moved an important admin
note about not using nova-network if using the
Networking service into Introduction for better
visibility.

Change-Id: I6eb5fa90845d67e5db8958c0af88142ed2a52eab
implements: blueprint user-guides-reorganised

I have instances with Debian Jessie created with the debian element:

 $ cat /etc/cloud/cloud.cfg.d/01_hostname.cfg
 hostname: debian

Turns out in Jessie cloud-init 0.7.6 ignores cloud metadata whenever hostname or fqdn are set in a config file.

Roughly:

 # no fqdn set, get fqdn from cloud
 # get hostname from cfg if available otherwise cloud
 fqdn = cloud.get_hostname(fqdn=True)
 if "hostname" in cfg:
     # hashar: set from config file NOT cloud
     hostname = cfg['hostname']
 else:
     # fallback to cloud
     hostname = cloud.get_hostname()


Relevant code is https://github.com/number5/cloud-init/blob/0.7.6/cloudinit/util.py#L839-L860'}, {'account_id': 2475, 'date': '2015-10-30 21:42:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

https://review.openstack.org/240614  proposes to have "hostname: debian" to only by set for wheezy.'}]

commit_message:
Fix "(None)" seed hostname on Debian

The cloud-init package on Debian Linux overwrites the system
hostname to "(None)" unless a hostname is specified in one
of the /etc/cloud/cloud.cfg.d/* files. This change applies
a default hostname of "debian" using cloud-init.

Change-Id: I9b411df44cfa05f899e708900f95719c0bcd6267

commit_message:
Websocket Proxy should verify Origin header

If the Origin HTTP header passed in the WebSocket handshake does
not match the host, this could indicate an attempt at a
cross-site attack.  This commit adds a check to verify
the origin matches the host.

Change-Id: Ica6ec23d6f69a236657d5ba0c3f51b693c633649
Closes-Bug: 1409142

commit_message:
Providing more information about fail job

When job if failed, we can see only id. Is not good.
In this patch added information about job(name, type)
closes-bug: #1510611

Change-Id: I83d2f722259ff8e02071f8c74bed71756a856e17

commit_message:
Divide the test and the class with useful methods

Because CommandLine class used in
    create_backup_reset_restore_and_deploy_via_cli it should not have test
    decorator. Proboscis saves test function each time when module are
    imported

Change-Id: I30fd2596f03f10992b0d743c7e375325b45bf90c
Closes-bug: #1507999

commit_message:
Eager load snapshot_metadata in *snapshot_get_all

All methods returning snapshot lists in db.sqlalchemy.api are eager
loading snapshot_metadata - besides snapshot_get_all_by_project and
snapshot_get_active_by_window. In case of the latter that fact caused
unit tests to randomly fail because of SQLAlchemy Session sometimes
getting closed before the metadata got lazy loaded. This commit adds
missing options(joinedload('snapshot_metadata')) to these queries.

Change-Id: I72557ebc7af9f3044046965ca79c9fe7c15520fc
Closes-Bug: 1501838

commit_message:
Added missing HTTP verbs to the requests checks

According to http://docs.python-requests.org/en/latest/user/advanced/
requests supports many HTTP verbs, however bandit was checking for
use of only two (post and get) - this patch adds support for the
other verbs that requests supports today.

Change-Id: I57df1f1139def0c3663d2377eabbcbe9ca248146

commit_message:
Remove wrong paramter COMPUTE_API_VERSION

Since:
 - novaclient doesn't require specify the *compute api* version
  (default is 2.latest now)
 - novaclient doesn't use COMPUTE_API_VERSION, since it's wrong name(
   OS_COMPUTE_API_VERSION is a correct name)

we can remove COMPUTE_API_VERSION and NOVA_VERSION vars

Change-Id: I7b50cdacb5342806dae8621dca012b4b1de0a604

commit_message:
ABANDON: Parallelize spawn

Another attempt to parallelize some of the pieces of spawn.

Before:
Create -> PlugVifs -> PlugMgmtVif -> CreateDiskForImg -> ConnectDisk ->
ConnectVolume(1) -> SaveBDM(1) -> ConnectVolume(2) -> SaveBDM(2) ->
CreateAndConnectCfgDrive -> stg_ftsk -> UpdateIBMiSettings -> PowerOn

After:
                                  Create
                                 PlugVifs
           _____________________PlugMgmtVif______________
         /                        /    \                  \
        |                       /        \                 |
CreateDiskForImg   ConnectVolume(1)   ConnectVolume(2) CreateAndConnect-
   ConnectDisk        SaveBDM(1)         SaveBDM(2)       CfgDrive
        |                       \        /                 |
         \                        \    /                  /
           ----------------------stg_ftsk----------------
                            UpdateIBMiSettings
                                 PowerOn

ABANDON: This won't work - we must connect the storage in order.

Change-Id: I0ecce0ab8de2a2ff78a84dfb55490c930697abe0

commit_message:
Use correct constraint for allowed_address_pairs

Use constraint 'net_cidr' instead of 'ip_addr' for
ip_address in allowed_address_pairs because ip_address
accept a cidr as parameter.[1]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/8c3cb79aa54b0ffcdc840c7e95ab809835d05001/neutron/extensions/allowedaddresspairs.py#L85-L90

Closes-Bug: #1509962
Change-Id: Ica3ef0aa7a3ccab2a69e4f1e5bdb7bbd00e0699b

Murano CI Rework: Move test execution and log collection into separate scripts

 - Move test execution into run_tests.sh

commit_message:
Add support for elasticsearch number of replicas

It is now possible to specify the number of replicas of the freezer
index in the elasticsearch database.

The value is set by the freezer-db-init script and can be specified
either as a command line parameter or defined in the freezer-api config
file.

When not specified it is set to the default value 2.

Adds the following command line parameter to the freeze-db-init script:

    -r  --replicas <N>

Adds the following parameter to the [storage] group of the
freezer-api.conf file:

    number_of_replicas = N

Change-Id: I210dce8bf634727f52c87152c3d036cc4d7065b5

commit_message:
Replace timeutils.isotime() with datetime.isoformat()

We deprecated timeutils.isotime since oslo.utils 1.6.0,
this commit replaces it.

Change-Id: Iadefe5823cd5ba9f388dbe854c441e8858120d7f
Related-Bug: #1479056

commit_message:
Make several attempts to attach image file

If one starts 2 or more instances of fuel-agent simultaneously, then
fuel-agent could fail on loop device allocation. With this patch it
makes several attempts to attach temporary image file to loop device.

Change-Id: I502eb07a69a2d813157d7511fc03032671e98196
Closes-Bug: #1506071

commit_message:
Access the Ubuntu and MOS APT repos via the master node

Thus slave nodes don't have to have a route to archive.ubuntu.com
(or configure APT to use HTTP proxy).

Depends-On: I97073d9baec9ceb6ee5b4843a837e2a9e5cbcc9f
Change-Id: I14e892d278aaaabe5cb596e75e4bbafdb2c44d5a

commit_message:
nailgun::nginx: reverse proxy Ubuntu and MOS repositories

Thus the slave nodes can access Ubuntu and MOS repositories via
http://${MASTER_NODE_IP}:8080/mirror/archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
and
http://${MASTER_NODE_IP}:8080/mirror/mirror.fuel-infra.org/mos-repos/
URLs, respectively. This way the slave nodes don't have to have a route
to archive.ubuntu.com (or a nearest Ubuntu APT repo). The actual Ubuntu
and MOS mirrors can be set in astute.yaml using the MIRROR_UBUNTU and
MIRROR_MOS variables.

DocImpact: MIRROR_UBUNTU, MIRROR_MOS - default Ubuntu and MOS mirrors

Partial-Bug: #1460169
Change-Id: I97073d9baec9ceb6ee5b4843a837e2a9e5cbcc9f

commit_message:
Allow custom private network name

Private network name "net04" should now use
customizable value configured in nailgun.
If this value is not present in nailgun, it
defaults back to "net04".

Change-Id: I66b7cde820c114b9c447fc4c169a51d3a63d0bea
Partial-Bug: #1349702

Get predifened net name from nailgun

Neutron predefined network names
like net04 and net04_ext can be modified,
so we need get such data from nailgun

commit_message:
Added precommit and postcommit hooks in ovsvapp mech_driver

This patch-set added the precommit and postcommit methods for network,
subnet and port in ovsvapp mechanism driver which is required by
ovsvapp driver[1].

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/239916/

Change-Id: I3f36e6c1dcc5d10cf2c630d8246f233c726dfbd4

commit_message:
Execute extra commands for diagnostic snapshot

Gather additional info from nodes for diagnostic
snapshot:

* IP configuration inside network namespaces
* network stats (sockets) inside network namespaces
* current ARP table state

Change-Id: Ifbd0cb672c43728e41f6b33417da578c42a3031f
Closes-bug: #1508458

With this patch the scripts are generated by automatically
only from setuptools. The /bin/freezerc script is removed
and the content is incorporated in freezer.main

This patch should make more portable freezer on
win32 platform.

Unfortunately in order to support win32 platforms
we need to use a version of PBR >= 1.0.0,

commit_message:
Improved freezerc and freezer-agent script management

With this patch the scripts are generated by automatically
only from setuptools. The /bin/freezerc script is removed
and the content is incorporated in freezer.main

This patch should make more portable freezer on
win32 platform.

Unfortunately in order to support win32 platforms
we need to use a version of PBR >= 1.0.0,
to support env markers. Now requirements.txt reflects that

Change-Id: I31a4a13711f8c042072e3cc8785078fdbb971cb7

commit_message:
Fixed bug on requierments and deps

For some reason PBR wasn't installing the
packages listed in requirements.txt. By adding
explicitly the pbr version in setup.py and
adding setuptools requirements the issue is fixed.

Change-Id: Iccb66ae20a7108fe7f359ae656ed11c4e5d6f7a0

[{'created': '2015-10-27 14:13:02.000000000', 'message': 'Try to revert patches to Puppet modules every time

If octane command was interrupted or failed before patches
to puppet were reverted, the patch will be applied and repeated
command will fail.

Try to revert the patch every time before apply it and skip
failures. Only actually apply the patch if revert is not assumed.

Change-Id: I5719dba3c621f307fe5d6ae2356f15d38ee28ff9
'}]
commit_message:
Try to revert patches to Puppet modules every time

If octane command was interrupted or failed before patches
to puppet were reverted, the patch will be applied and repeated
command will fail.

Try to revert the patch every time before apply it and skip
failures. Only actually apply the patch if revert is not assumed.

Change-Id: I5719dba3c621f307fe5d6ae2356f15d38ee28ff9

commit_message:
Add SerializerNotSupported error type to nailgun.errors

Now in case when type of task is not known to Nailgun proper error is
thrown.

Change-Id: I33923c04e3eba0ed8028efac51e36f347296d0ae
Closes-Bug: #1506915

commit_message:
[Ironic] build bootstrap

 install additional packages to mcollective container:
  - fuel-agent-bootstrap-ironic-configs
  - fuel-bootstrap-image-builder
 add upload image task

Partially Implements: blueprint fuel-integrate-ironic
Depends-On: I99c9c8081a277431cf3fe65703059962cae3c746
Change-Id: I01354d8865f99d3587cf315f7d28d30dae72d375

ironic-api task implements:

* create 'baremetal' flat network in neutron, which maps to baremetal network
 on infra nodes

* upload bootstrap kernel and initramfs to glance

"}, {'created': '2015-07-17 07:21:18.000000000', 'message': "Enable ironic in MOS

This change adds new following tasks:
* ironic-db - create database for ironic
* ironic-vips - create resources in pacemaker for VIPs for baremetal network
* ironic-api - deploys API service, configure keystone auth, registers secret
key for Swift tempurl, creates 'baremetal' flat network in neutron, which maps
to baremetal network on infra nodes
* ironic-conductor - deploys conductor service and tftp server for PXE boot
* ironic-compute - deploys nova-compute service with ironic compute driver

ironic-conductor and ironic-compute combined to one group 'ironic', which
mapped to 'ironic' node role

Implemets: blueprint fuel-integrate-ironic (partially)

Change-Id: I168e7b831ccf12a9b3c7faf7063133ddf12ab670

"}, {'created': '2015-07-22 09:17:45.000000000', 'message': "Enable ironic in MOS

This change adds new following tasks:
* ironic-db - create database for ironic
* ironic-vips - create resources in pacemaker for VIPs for baremetal network
* ironic-api - deploys API service, configure keystone auth, registers secret
key for Swift tempurl, creates 'baremetal' flat network in neutron, which maps
to baremetal network on infra nodes
* ironic-conductor - deploys conductor service and tftp server for PXE boot
* ironic-compute - deploys nova-compute service with ironic compute driver

ironic-conductor and ironic-compute combined to one group 'ironic', which
mapped to 'ironic' node role

Co-Authored-By: Vasyl Saienko <vsaienko@mirantis.com>

Implemets: blueprint fuel-integrate-ironic (partially)

Change-Id: I168e7b831ccf12a9b3c7faf7063133ddf12ab670

commit_message:
[Ironic] Add Ironic API service

Following tasks introduces:
* ironic-api - API service for Ironic
* ironic-db - create and configure database for Ironic
* ironic-keystone - create service and endpoints in Keystone
* ironic-post-swift-key - post secret key for Swift tempurl

Partially Implemets: blueprint fuel-integrate-ironic

Change-Id: I168e7b831ccf12a9b3c7faf7063133ddf12ab670

Migration test for 8.0 fixed

Result of uuid.uuid4 casted to text before insertiation to DB.
str() replaced with six.text_type()

commit_message:
Rename context.py to logs.py

At one point this file contained the context for logging, but
the reason for its existence is now for logging.

Implements: blueprint logging-migration

Change-Id: I4ba42bbef97b09d31236ac8c01b6fb23827b8bee

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html

the current copy_image_to_volume method of sheepdogdriver can only
write the image file to local sheepdog, with this patch, it supports

commit_message:
optimize the copy_image_to_volume method of sheepdogdriver

the current copy_image_to_volume method of sheepdogdriver can only
write the image file to local sheepdog, with this patch, it supports
write image file to remote sheepdog node.

Closes-Bug: #1509910
Change-Id: I5084ef2c048439ad8b9d6ae56ce8cccaadc26262

commit_message:
Add net_cidr constraint for destination of subnet

Neutron allows cidr format of 'host_routes: destination"
for subnet, add net_cidr constraint for it.

Change-Id: Id3c8ba4e8c4b4279882739f4511e5994a17845d9

It's a common practice to put example file to /usr/share/doc to
give users access to all available settings.

commit_message:
Move variables from plugin.sh to settings

Global variables are the same as settings and should be
in plugin settings file.
This patch moves variables from plugin.sh to settings file.
Also add a few comments for variables groups for better understanding
for what specific variable is responsible.

Change-Id: I47aef3b047ce11a5729643353e801eee963e4e76
Closes-Bug: #1510744

commit_message:
Allow debug to be set in configuration file

The current default value for debug in cliff is False.  Cloud
config assumes that it was set that way on the command line and
does not overlay it with the value from the configuration file.
Cliff bug:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/python-cliff/+bug/1483378

Change-Id: I66d82b489b2241dbcd1e1350e94259a54ce09de7

commit_message:
Add basic renderspec test integration

Use renderspec to render the jinja2 templates into real RPM spec
files. Abort if the conversion doesn't work.

Change-Id: I31edbe16129a627236db0c980602ca23a0ba2a4a

commit_message:
Add plugin cookiecutter in documentation

Since we have a official cookiecutter project we should
rely on it in the documentation. All titles are moved a bit
since only the usage of the cookiecutter and the entry point
is needed to create a working test project. All other information
is just additional and not mandatory for plugin creation.

Change-Id: Ia04d2ea747f19d7b1d272bd7664ff05f61c7c88c

commit_message:
Clean up some Instancev1 stuff in the tests

This cleans up some instance verification tests to be explicit about using
the base class. We're getting lucky right now, which is why this is working,
but some stuff coming in oslo.versionedobjects will change some behavior
around backporting which will make this fail.

Change-Id: I56c3f6bfc1829671a6f8ea958bd07afe7331753e

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-01 14:29:51.000000000', 'message': "Promote an arbitrary string to be a docstring

In https://review.openstack.org/#/c/229857/ , Lance pointed out that the
string here was not being caught by pep257, and that turned out to be
because it wasn't actually a docstring at all.

This appears to have been intended as a module-level docstring, but
because it's not the first element in the module, it's actually just a
regular string, and thus not validated against PEP257.

However, rather than promoting this to be a module-level docstring, the
actual content refers to the Saml2 class itself (going so far as to note
the class inheritance and class path for configuration), and thus it
makes sense to make it a class-level docstring.

Change-Id: Ie6250613291c07d4c1a41104453a590fc3a65382

commit_message:
Promote an arbitrary string to be a docstring

In https://review.openstack.org/#/c/229857/ , Lance pointed out that the
string here was not being caught by pep257, and that turned out to be
because it wasn't actually a docstring at all.

This appears to have been intended as a module-level docstring, but
because it's not the first element in the module, it's actually just a
regular string, and thus not validated against PEP257.

However, rather than promoting this to be a module-level docstring, the
actual content refers to the Saml2 class itself (going so far as to note
the class inheritance and class path for configuration), and thus it
makes sense to make it a class-level docstring.

Change-Id: Ie6250613291c07d4c1a41104453a590fc3a65382

commit_message:
Switch to using pbr version for cli version string

This commit switches from using the hard coded version strings in the
cliff main app to using the version string generated pbr. This means
that the version returned from --version on the tempest cli will
actually reflect the version of the code you're using.

Change-Id: I74b2a2c4f1cf9b4a6639c35545b3256ea94cd961

commit_message:
Use Tempest-lib's compute hypervisor_client

Compute hypervisor_client has been migrated to
tempest-lib- I1a1dcab8ecd6e12ec03d14303517c8cb1e68ec60

Now Tempest-lib provides this client as stable interface so Tempest
should start using this from lib and remove its own copy.
Also remove its unit tests.

This commits makes Tempest to use compute hypervisor_client
from Tempest-lib.

Change-Id: I529b3e359250443b2c27b877bf82522102e6a1fb

commit_message:
Add puppet-syntax development dependency

Without this patch, 'rake lint' was failing because the puppet-syntax gem was not installed.

$ bundle exec rake lint
rake aborted!
cannot load such file -- puppet-syntax/tasks/puppet-syntax
/home/francois/WORK/dev/openstack/puppet-horizon/Rakefile:3:in `require'
/home/francois/WORK/dev/openstack/puppet-horizon/Rakefile:3:in `<top (required)>'
(See full trace by running task with --trace)
$

Change-Id: Id0df9a0c0f912b34e8031b8a2ff5f1b73fa1ec38

commit_message:
shorter sleeps if metadata changes are detected

This patch updates os-collect-config so that the sleep interval
time is shortened if changes are detected. This should decrease
deployment time when using Heat templates which use depends_on
to step through a sequence of software deployment resources.

The new default sleep is set to 1 and increases
by sleep_time *= 2 until it reaches the default
sleep interval again.

Change-Id: I5cbd0956db2abebec876b15bee72b70ec64d5aef

commit_message:
This patch allows for tenant filtering. For example:
    nova list --tenant <tenant_id>
Previously, tenant_id was accepted but did not give desirable output.
If you don't pass tenant_id, the current context tenant will be used.

Closes-Bug: #1398329

Change-Id: I1c134038b6b30c98495018108e839fac29fa3311

commit_message:
Changed backporting of embedded Network object when backporting a FixedIP

When backporting a FixedIP object to the version 1.1 and less
we must backport Network object to version 1.1, because since
version 1.2, FixedIp object uses Network object v1.2.

The following two commits changed version of Network to v1.2,
but these commits do NOT dump FixedIp version:

275a165cf0e74112d7ec9addacb1f84d703977c8

ad6051bb5c2b62a0de6708cd2d7ac1e3cfd8f1d3

In fact we had to add two new versions of FixedIp
between v1.1 and v1.2, but we forgot about dumping when we
changed Network version.

This backporting is needed when we use Icehouse compute.
In this case nova-conductor sends back
a FixedIP object of version 1.1 with an embedded Network
object of 1.2, Icehouse then incorrectly tries to backport
the FixedIP object again (as opposed to the Network object)
leading to a loop.

Related-Bug: #1408498

Change-Id: I5f9fad8228e23457a878e533a0e3d1faf54ee460

commit_message:
Remove the destination volume check in delete_volume

* If the volume migration fails in the middle of the progress,
the destination volume will be cleaned up via
rpcapi.delete_volume. The method delete_volume in manager
should allow us to clean up the database record for the
destination volume.

* The variable update in migrate_volume_completion has been
assigned twice. Remove the second one.

Change-Id: Icb815476943053f1487268b33c28f3575c4fd0dc
Closes-Bug: #1490445

commit_message:
Stop running noop against fuel-web

Fuel web has real jobs on some branches and noop on others. The problem
with this is it slows down everyone using noop in the gate because they
share a queue with fuel-web which runs jobs.

Remove the noop job from fuel-web entirely and force them to run pep8 on
the stable branches. This is largely arbitrary but it is trivial to get
a passing pep8 job on old code (just ignore the pep8 rules that fail) so
should be a good choice for them.

Change-Id: I9c77e84c089d5623dcdb047b2402028db77096df

https://github.com/openstack/cinder/blob/master/cinder/db/sqlalchemy/api.py#L1344

You just updated the migration part, this will not fix the complete problem. The NULL identity key problem occurs when _volume_get_query() is called in other scenario. 

Maybe we can fix it by set the joint loosely.That means if volume type is null, no joint volume_type table.'}, {'account_id': 15961, 'date': '2015-10-14 08:08:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Please help me to clear the above concerns. I will remove -1 if I am wrong.'}, {'account_id': 2861, 'date': '2015-10-14 08:19:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

The issue is raised where exactly as you said.

Howver, I add a param joined_load. During finish_volume_migration, this param is set to False, when calling _volume_get.
 
So _volume_get_query will return model_query(context, models.Volume, session=session, project_only=project_only) and it won't reach the line https://github.com/openstack/cinder/blob/master/cinder/db/sqlalchemy/api.py#L1344 as you mentioned. This way prevents all the models, like CG, metadata, volume type, etc, from being loaded."}, {'account_id': 10621, 'date': '2015-10-14 08:51:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I would like to see a comment, maybe in a doc string for the method _volume_get_query(), explaining the the parameter joined_load is to allow for the special case of migration, where the volume model only is being updated, so the other models are not required.'}, {'account_id': 9535, 'date': '2015-10-14 09:12:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

?: If I understand the bug exception correctly the error is caused because we are trying to assign an ORM object to a backref field, right?  If that's the case, why isn't that field being excluded by:

 or not is_column(dest_volume_ref, key)):

Since that is the purpose of that line, to avoid copying non DB fields..."}, {'account_id': 2861, 'date': '2015-10-15 02:17:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

@Gorka, it really has nothing to do with not is_column(dest_volume_ref, key). What the source or destination volume ref will be depends on models.Volume, the model itself.

Let's take volume type as the example, though this issue is not limited to it. Get the src volume via src_volume_ref = _volume_get(...) and get the dest volume via dest_volume_ref = _volume_get. The result will be something like:

{id: 'volume-id', ... , volume_type_id: 'volume-type-id', 'volume_type': <content of volume-type-model>}

for both of the src and destination volumes, if we joinedload the model from other tables. The fields, volume_type_id and volume_type co-exist in the queried results and they are correlated to each other.

If we retype from NULL type to another type, the volume_type_id will be changed from non-NULL to NULL for the dest volume result during setattr(dest_volume_ref, key, value_to_dst), which means volume_type_id becomes none, but volume_type still not none. Then we will have the errors as reported.

Hope this is a clear explanation."}, {'account_id': 2861, 'date': '2015-10-15 05:46:13.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-15 06:57:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Verified+1

After a successful volume migration, the source volume and the

model only and there is no need to load other models, like
volume type, metadata, consistency group, etc. If we load

commit_message:
Remove the jointly loaded model in finish_volume_migration

After a successful volume migration, the source volume and the
destination volume need to swap the data in the models in
finish_volume_migration. It is sufficient to load the volume
model only and there is no need to load other models, like
volume type, metadata, consistency group, etc. If we load
these additional models, it will lead to NULL key error, when
either source or destination model has a NULL key pointer.

Change-Id: I04ad0739387d602719591680854e6655cc87f9ab
Closes-Bug: #1505572

commit_message:
Add -constraints sections for CI jobs

Tox does not currently support using factors with sections, and work
towards enabling this has stalled, as such we will need to duplicate
sections adding -constraints to facilitate running sections with the
constrained install_command.

Implements Blueprint: Requirements-Management

Change-Id: Icbbb78cfcd074b0050e60c54557637af723f9b92

commit_message:
Fix parameter_defaults for comma_delimited_list and json

When environment of a stack contained a parameter_defaults section with
a value for a parameter of type comma_delimited_list or json, that default
didn't get applied unless in a nested stack.

The issue was that CommaDelimitedListParam contains a variable to cache
its value, and that cache was only created upon creation of a
CommaDelimitedListParam object, but it wasn't updated on `set_default`
method call. The cache now updates on `set_default` too.

Co-Authored-By: Steven Hardy <shardy@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I85b13a79dbc97a77e20c0d5df8eaf05b3000815e
Closes-Bug: #1504137
(cherry picked from commit 3827c61b25fa86c1f9882be15caf27d2efa6c4fe)

commit_message:
Remove typos in murano-* and rally-murano jobs definitions

Murano plugin should be enabled only for liberty and upper branches.
Enabling plugin in any case make murano gates in kilo branch to mailfunction.
This patch removes extra lines with enable-plugin functions.

Change-Id: I23dd8a75f968fbef773b4265a5e6941a70dda280

commit_message:
Add sort options to columns in tests page

Now is possible to order tests table for each one of its fields as well
search for a specific test by name.

subject: Replace x.keys() with six.iterkeys(x)
messages:
[{'account_id': 15699, 'date': '2015-08-11 10:55:23.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2015-08-11 11:22:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

Hi Sonu,

Thanks for the patch. I marked inline the places I think it's fine to use the six.iterkeys().

The other places I don't see the reason of using it (maybe I'm missing something and you can explain it to me). For i.e:

Why use an iterator that will be converted to a list that will then be sorted if just using sorted() in either a list (py2) or an iterator (py3) will have the same result (it will return a sorted list).

Same for set() the input for set can be either a list or an iterator.

So those bits I don't get why we need to use six.iterkeys()"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-08-11 11:47:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified-1

commit_message:
Replace x.keys() with six.iterkeys(x)

This patch replaces x.keys with six.iterkeys(x)
to provide py 2/3 compatibility.

Change-Id: Ie6665fc3ece5513ecbade0a658e58185b6968b23

commit_message:
Wait for FC multipath devices to become writable

Sometimes the multipath devices would be read-only block devices which
would end up causing problems when anything tries to write to them. We
now will wait and rescan a few times to try and get them to become
read-write before moving on with the attach.

Change-Id: If3c17348f6a6e766f811fcd446c03c82e5c8a883
Partial-Bug: #1495701
(cherry picked from commit 2e514655194b5385526dec7bc743cd3500a4dca9)

I think there might be something mislead you from the following patch (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/134124)?

Something not working here is keystone wsgi middleware (https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/master/keystone/common/wsgi.py#L392) but the app and third party middlewares still working with the local conf. I think stanek has the some comments about this in the lauchpad, This is reason why we deprecate them.

The history of this bug and the patch here has lasted almost one year, just abandon this old and propose this.

So, something I tried includes, 'not support local conf' -> 'deprecate the local conf and remove all of the relevant comments' -> 'just deprecate the local conf'. So, what the next? not deprecate them and remove all of the comments?

Since Keystone's paste.deploy configuration file has been separated
from main Keystone configuration file, "keystone.conf", all of
local configuration or driver-specific configuration parameters
should go to main Keystone configuration file instead of PasteDeploy
conf file, i.e. configuration within the "keystone-paste.ini"
is not (and will not) be supported.

This patch set intent to remove the legacy code which may cause user
confusion when some newbies start to work and deploy keystone
service in OpenStack.

This patch set is code specific changes in order to make usage more
clear, documentation specific change is submitted in another patch.

'}, {'created': '2015-04-23 06:39:41.000000000', 'message': 'Remove local conf information from paste-ini

Since keystone's paste.deploy configuration file has been separated
from the main keystone configuration file, "keystone.conf", all
local configuration or driver-specific configuration parameters
must go in the main keystone configuration file instead of PasteDeploy
conf file.

As we are not sure if there are deployers or thirdparty middlewares
still need Paste for local configuration, and it works for application
or third-party middleware so far, thus, in this patch we just accept the
local conf in the WSGI middleware to avoid WSGI middleware's broken
and log some warning message.

This patch set is code specific changes in order to make usage more
clear and fix the WSGI middleware broken issue when local conf is given.
Documentation specific change is submitted in another
patch(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/134125/).

commit_message:
Fix the issues found with local conf

Since keystone's paste.deploy configuration file has been separated
from the main keystone configuration file (keystone.conf), all
local configuration or driver-specific configuration parameters
must be in the main keystone configuration file instead of PasteDeploy
conf file.

This patch changes to log a warning if there's any local_conf defined in
PasteDeploy INI and remove `local_config` argument from wsgi middleware
since it doesn't work.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1369388

commit_message:
Refactor configuring cluster network settings

Change default values for networking accordingly
to the existing networks
Apply defaults for new created cluster instead of
reconfiguring all networks

Change-Id: I3eb3c6bdd9128c4e35741884daf0793714ce3b7c
Closes-Bug: 1476185
Co-Authored-By: Vladimir Khlyunev <vkhlyunev@mirantis.com>

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

commit_message:
Add the missing parameter

The kwargs parameter missed in the init method of class
Middleware will break the paste pipeline if there is any
local config defined in the `keystone-paste.ini` file.

This patch adds that missing parameter.

Change-Id: I8cea8529eb752359fc4abf79433d26062234206a
Closes-Bug: #1369388

This is the first draft of the priorities for Mitaka. It's not
exhaustive and it needs to be discussed thoroughly. It'd be great to
start elaborating on it before the summit and agreed on the final list
at the summit.

For this cycle, I believe we're should be more strict on what is/isn't a
priority. Considering the latest feedback from the community and our
current team, we ought to be very careful.

This list, however, does not exclude other works. It just clarifies what
the teams priorities are and where most of the time should probably go.

commit_message:
Add Glance priorities for Mitaka

For this cycle, I believe we should be more strict on what is/isn't a
priority. Considering the latest feedback from the community and our
current team, we ought to be very careful.

This list does not exclude other works. It just clarifies what
the teams priorities are and where most of the time should probably go.

Also, this list does not define features and it doesn't replace specs.
Specs *must* be written and they'll be referenced in this list.

Change-Id: I312d0dcd815da10f083f2fb2a673f7c192c231f4

commit_message:
Add nova-powervm translation domain

Since nova-powervm is not in tree with nova, it can't use nova's
translation domain.  This change introduces i18n.py and the
nova-powervm domain.

Change-Id: I9d3565e6ad1737629350fe02c7a41d56b0cf401a
(cherry picked from commit ded3c4b7ca8757e789bcdcaa2d10dbfa016a813c)

commit_message:
Add base devstack plugins support

Add support for installing networking powervm through the devstack
plugins infrastructure. This allows you to simply enable the plugin
in a devstack localrc, provide any non-default config, and run
stack.sh to configure/install it.
- Added plugin files
- Added README
- Added bashate to tox test environments for scripts

Change-Id: Ie56b279d38c3fdba7971b231470c17dea22156e2

commit_message:
Update Configuring Keystone doc for consistency

Character between section name and parameter name is
backslash or white space in Configuring Keystone doc.
This patch change backslash to white space for consistency.

Change-Id: I730a9769dad117ab2f94619bd02ae2a00c30bc38

commit_message:
Load the QoS notification driver

The agent based RPC notification driver for message queue is the default.
Added support for multiple notification drivers.

Change-Id: Ie18a2877c42731e01e9aec61e1aaf83d6f785d5d
Closes-Bug:1479547

commit_message:
Update plugin registry - s/stackforge/openstack

The 'stackforge' namespace has been removed, and all plugins are now
inside the 'openstack' namespace.

Change-Id: I9deae235da7ef907a8d9d915d57257fecca3b544

commit_message:
Add text for deprecated parameter

Add information for "max_fixed_ips_per_port" option that the
option is deprecated and will be removed in the N release.

Co-Authored-By: Takanori Miyagishi <miyagishi.t@jp.fujitsu.com>

Change-Id: I9aa876c371e7b6cff2068dc641c5e4b5ebda8001
Closes-Bug: #1503088

commit_message:
Truncate 'input' data in the wf/action update command output

Items can have a list of input values, to show them all in the
command output table is not a good idea.
This commit added another type of formatting to the 'workflow-update'
and 'action-update' commands output and appropriate functional tests
that check it.

Change-Id: I37db7f0a32968077693b18924353900878556170

commit_message:
Remove bad ca_status validator. Always reject CA

Remove a validator which has been marked for an update for some time.
CA certificate signing should not be handled by Anchor at all.

Change-Id: Ib13a0ca3445956e35c23c559f59f37e6721c1a33
Closes-bug: 1508776

commit_message:
Raise oslo.serialization version in requirements

We started using oslo_serialization.jsonutils.dump_as_bytes() in test
in commit Ib30c701b9dbbcc774dfc5f19a7174ab318006206. This method got
added in oslo.serialization 1.10, so we need to update the version of
the library in order to reflect actual requirements.

Depends-On: I123159e1a3ae3b166918513545f1b5835cfb4782
Change-Id: I411daf355816f76078f56196635e4136b0c9722e
